      • toDominoFriendly

        protected static Object toDominoFriendly(Object value,
                                         Base context,
                                         Collection<lotus.domino.Base> recycleThis)
                                  throws IllegalArgumentException

        Attempts to convert a provided scalar value to a "Domino-friendly" data type like DateTime, String, etc. Currently, the data types supported are the already-Domino-friendly ones, Number, Date, Calendar, and CharSequence.

        Parameters:
        value - The incoming non-collection value
        context - The context Base object, for finding the correct session
        Returns:
        The Domino-friendly conversion of the object, or the object itself if it is already usable.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - When the object is not convertible.
